text: Théodore Wichwael, O.S.A. or Dietrich Wichwael (died 1519) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Auxiliary Bishop of Cologne (1504–1519)."Bishop Théodore Wichwael, O.S.A." Catholic-Hierarchy.org. David M. Cheney. Retrieved March 21, 2016 ==Biography== Théodore Wichwael was appointed a priest in the Order of Saint Augustine. On 2 Aug 1504, he was appointed during the papacy of Pope Julius II as Auxiliary Bishop of Cologne and Titular Bishop of Cyrene. He served as Auxiliary Bishop of Cologne until his death on 3 Mar 1519. == References == ==External links and additional sources== * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) Category:16th-century Roman Catholic bishops Category:Bishops appointed by Pope Julius II Category:1519 deaths Category:Augustinian bishops
